The IP-XACT file is used to configure the pck600_lpd_q. The configuration options are:

SEQUENCER          :  Configures the lpd_q as a sequencer or expander. Default value is 0. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the SEQUENCER verilog parameter.

NUM_QCHL           :  Configures the number of Q-Channel devices. Default value is 2. Range is 2 to 32. This maps to the NUM_QCHL verilog parameter.

CTRL_Q_CH_SYNC     :  Includes or excludes synchronizers on CTRL Q-Channel. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the CTRL_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

DEV_Q_CH_SYNC      :  Includes or excludes synchronizers on DEV Q-Channel. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the DEV_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

DEV_QACTIVE_SYNC   : Includes or excludes synchronizers on Device Qactive. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the DEV_QACTIVE_SYNC verilog parameter.

ACTIVE_DENY        :  Enables or disables ACTIVE deny support. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the ACTIVE_DENY verilog parameter.




